text:
Was in town for a night, and glad to say my stay here was a very good experience. 
Here's why:
1) front desk staff was incredibly nice and helpful;
2) room was clean and well-appointed (ironing board, lots of hangers in the small armoir);
3) bed was comfortable;
4) room was quiet even though I was only a few floors up, and right on 35th St. 

Four stars instead of five because it's a decent-sized hotel but only 2 elevators, which meant a long morning wait (I gave up after 5 mins. and took the stairs). Small 'price' to pay for an overall great experience.
